# do.word — what DO is: to change the world.
# Axiom: bottoms out in the host (the DO verb and its ops, each written as a fact through the
# stamper). Descends from word.word, base.word, chain.word, fold.word. Every word
# grounded (do, fact, fold, world). This word DECLARES the verb. Who may do is a grant, held
# through `can`, declared later. Be and name also make facts, of a presence and an identity.
# A do is the change of the world. A do may act on a being and still not be a call. A call is a
# do too, but the one form that also carries a said to a being's inbox and wakes its cognition
# to answer, through machinery beyond the stamper. That is why call earns its own word, told there.

To do is to stamp a word; the do makes the world after.
A do makes a fact, and a fold reads it. The world after is not the world before.
The fact a do makes is a see or a do.
A do has many forms. To make, to give, to take, to set, to move, to grant, and to drop are dos.
To be is a do on a being; to name is a do on a name.
Each form, and the thing it acts on, takes its name where that thing is.
